---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout
    title="LSCSS Tools and Demos"
    description="Interactive tools and demos for learning Layered Semantic CSS."
>
    <section class="site-hero">
        <p class="eyebrow">Tools</p>

        <h1>
            Tools and demos
        </h1>

        <p class="intro">
            Interactive examples for exploring specificity, scope, container
            queries, accessibility, performance, browser support, and render
            behaviour.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="content-block">
        <h2>
            Start here
        </h2>

        <div class="hub-card-grid">
            <article class="hub-card">
                <h3>
                    <a href="/tools/specificity-calculator/">Specificity calculator</a>
                </h3>

                <p>
                    Compare selector weight and understand why short selectors
                    can still lose to higher-specificity rules.
                </p>
            </article>

            <article class="hub-card">
                <h3>
                    <a href="/tools/scope-demo/">Scope demo</a>
                </h3>

                <p>
                    See how scoped CSS can reduce naming noise while keeping
                    component boundaries clearer.
                </p>
            </article>

            <article class="hub-card">
                <h3>
                    <a href="/tools/container-query-visualiser/">Container query visualiser</a>
                </h3>

                <p>
                    Resize a component container and see why container queries
                    are useful for portable UI systems.
                </p>
            </article>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-block">
        <h2>
            Architecture and debugging
        </h2>

        <div class="hub-card-grid">
            <article class="hub-card">
                <h3><a href="/tools/specificity-graph/">Specificity graph</a></h3>
                <p>Visualise selector pressure and how specificity builds across a project.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="hub-card">
                <h3><a href="/tools/devtools-inspector/">DevTools-style inspector</a></h3>
                <p>Explore how layers, selectors, and overrides can be explained during debugging.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="hub-card">
                <h3><a href="/specificity-visualiser/">Specificity visualiser</a></h3>
                <p>Compare selector approaches such as component selectors, :where(), and @scope.</p>
            </article>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-block">
        <h2>
            Accessibility and browser support
        </h2>

        <div class="hub-card-grid">
            <article class="hub-card">
                <h3><a href="/tools/accessibility-demos/">Accessibility demos</a></h3>
                <p>Review focus styles, reduced motion, logical properties, and interaction states.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="hub-card">
                <h3><a href="/tools/browser-support-demos/">Browser support demos</a></h3>
                <p>Explore progressive enhancement and feature-based support decisions.</p>
            </article>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-block">
        <h2>
            Performance and rendering
        </h2>

        <div class="hub-card-grid">
            <article class="hub-card">
                <h3><a href="/tools/performance-demos/">Performance demos</a></h3>
                <p>Compare bundle size, third-party CSS isolation, and architectural performance trade-offs.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="hub-card">
                <h3><a href="/tools/render-performance-demos/">Render performance demos</a></h3>
                <p>Compare animation choices, containment, layout cost, and paint behaviour.</p>
            </article>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-block">
        <h2>
            Playgrounds
        </h2>

        <div class="hub-card-grid">
            <article class="hub-card">
                <h3><a href="/playground/">Playground</a></h3>
                <p>Try simple LSCSS component patterns and naming structures.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="hub-card">
                <h3><a href="/playground/live-editor/">Live editor</a></h3>
                <p>Edit CSS directly and see the result on a live component example.</p>
            </article>
        </div>
    </section>
</DocsLayout>
